{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Hcu8Zae33ebapyScTvHJ8h","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package prompt\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"bufio\"\n     5→\t\"bytes\"\n     6→\t\"context\"\n     7→\t\"encoding/json\"\n     8→\t\"fmt\"\n     9→\t\"log\"\n    10→\t\"os\"\n    11→\t\"os/exec\"\n    12→\t\"path/filepath\"\n    13→\t\"strconv\"\n    14→\t\"strings\"\n    15→\n    16→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n    17→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/protocol\"\n    18→)\n    19→\n    20→// DefaultAgentArgs maps known agent commands to their default arguments.\n    21→// Commands not in this map receive no default arguments (prompt on stdin only).\n    22→var DefaultAgentArgs = map[string][]string{\n    23→\t\"claude\": {\"-p\", \"--output-format\", \"stream-json\", \"--verbose\", \"--dangerously-skip-permissions\"},\n    24→\t\"gemini\": {\"-p\"},\n    25→\t\"codex\":  {\"--full-auto\"},\n    26→}\n    27→\n    28→type Adapter struct {\n    29→\tCommands     []string // ordered fallback chain of agent commands\n    30→\tExplicitArgs []string // if non-nil, overrides default args for all commands\n    31→\tRunID        string\n    32→\tStatusWriter *protocol.StatusWriter // optional: streams live output lines\n    33→}\n    34→\n    35→func New() *Adapter {\n    36→\treturn &Adapter{\n    37→\t\tCommands: []string{\"claude\"},\n    38→\t}\n    39→}\n    40→\n    41→func (a *Adapter) Name() string {\n    42→\treturn \"prompt\"\n    43→}\n    44→\n    45→// logMessage writes a message to the StatusWriter if available, otherwise to the standard logger.\n    46→func (a *Adapter) logMessage(stepName, msg string) {\n    47→\tif a.StatusWriter != nil {\n    48→\t\ta.StatusWriter.Log(stepName, msg)\n    49→\t} else {\n    50→\t\tlog.Println(msg)\n    51→\t}\n    52→}\n    53→\n    54→// argsFor returns the arguments for the given command. If ExplicitArgs is set,\n    55→// it is used for all commands. Otherwise, known agents get their default args.\n    56→func (a *Adapter) argsFor(command string) []string {\n    57→\tif a.ExplicitArgs != nil {\n    58→\t\treturn a.ExplicitArgs\n    59→\t}\n    60→\tif args, ok := DefaultAgentArgs[command]; ok {\n    61→\t\treturn args\n    62→\t}\n    63→\treturn nil\n    64→}\n    65→\n    66→// ParseCommands splits a comma-separated agent_command string into individual\n    67→// command names, trimming whitespace from each entry.\n    68→func ParseCommands(s string) []string {\n    69→\tparts := strings.Split(s, \",\")\n    70→\tvar cmds []string\n    71→\tfor _, p := range parts {\n    72→\t\tp = strings.TrimSpace(p)\n    73→\t\tif p != \"\" {\n    74→\t\t\tcmds = append(cmds, p)\n    75→\t\t}\n    76→\t}\n    77→\treturn cmds\n    78→}\n    79→\n    80→func (a *Adapter) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (string, error) {\n    81→\t// Check attempt count for retry limiting\n    82→\tif maxStr, ok := step.Config[\"max_attempts\"]; ok {\n    83→\t\tmax, err := strconv.Atoi(maxStr)\n    84→\t\tif err == nil {\n    85→\t\t\tcount := readAttemptCount(workDir, step.Name)\n    86→\t\t\tif count >= max {\n    87→\t\t\t\treturn \"give-up\", nil\n    88→\t\t\t}\n    89→\t\t}\n    90→\t}\n    91→\tincrementAttemptCount(workDir, step.Name)\n    92→\n    93→\t// Build the full prompt\n    94→\tfullPrompt, err := assemblePrompt(step, workDir, a.RunID)\n    95→\tif err != nil {\n    96→\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"assembling prompt: %w\", err)\n    97→\t}\n    98→\n    99→\t// Try each command in the fallback chain\n   100→\tvar lastResult string\n   101→\tvar lastStdout []byte\n   102→\tvar lastErr error\n   103→\tran := false\n   104→\n   105→\tfor i, command := range a.Commands {\n   106→\t\tresult, stdout, fallbackErr := a.tryCommand(ctx, command, fullPrompt, workDir, step.Name)\n   107→\t\tlastResult = result\n   108→\t\tlastStdout = stdout\n   109→\t\tlastErr = fallbackErr\n   110→\n   111→\t\tif fallbackErr == nil {\n   112→\t\t\tif i > 0 {\n   113→\t\t\t\tmsg := fmt.Sprintf(\"[fallback] step %q: using agent %q (primary agents failed)\", step.Name, command)\n   114→\t\t\t\ta.logMessage(step.Name, msg)\n   115→\t\t\t}\n   116→\t\t\tbreak\n   117→\t\t}\n   118→\t\tif stdout != nil {\n   119→\t\t\tran = true\n   120→\t\t}\n   121→\t\t// Log the fallback attempt\n   122→\t\tif i < len(a.Commands)-1 {\n   123→\t\t\tmsg := fmt.Sprintf(\"[fallback] step %q: agent %q failed (%v), trying %q\", step.Name, command, fallbackErr, a.Commands[i+1])\n   124→\t\t\ta.logMessage(step.Name, msg)\n   125→\t\t}\n   126→\t}\n   127→\n   128→\tif lastErr != nil && !ran && lastStdout == nil {\n   129→\t\t// All commands failed to produce any output (e.g., all not found)\n   130→\t\treturn \"\", lastErr\n   131→\t}\n   132→\n   133→\tresult := lastResult\n   134→\tif lastErr != nil {\n   135→\t\t// Last command in chain crashed without a result marker\n   136→\t\tresult = \"fail\"\n   137→\t}\n   138→\n   139→\t// Write output file\n   140→\toutputDir := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"output\")\n   141→\tif mkErr := os.MkdirAll(outputDir, 0755); mkErr == nil {\n   142→\t\t_ = os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(outputDir, step.Name+\".log\"), lastStdout, 0644)\n   143→\t}\n   144→\tprotocol.AppendHistory(workDir, step.Name, result, true, nil)\n   145→\treturn result, nil\n   146→}\n   147→\n   148→// tryCommand executes a single agent command and returns:\n   149→//   - result: the step result name (e.g. \"success\", \"fail\")\n   150→//   - stdout: captured stdout bytes\n   151→//   - fallbackErr: nil if the result is definitive, non-nil if fallback-eligible\n   152→//\n   153→// Fallback-eligible conditions:\n   154→//   - Command not found or failed to start (stdout will be nil)\n   155→//   - Command exited non-zero without a CLOCHE_RESULT marker\n   156→//\n   157→// Definitive (non-fallback) conditions:\n   158→//   - Command exited 0\n   159→//   - Command exited non-zero but produced a CLOCHE_RESULT marker\n   160→func (a *Adapter) tryCommand(ctx context.Context, command string, prompt string, workDir string, stepName string) (result string, stdout []byte, fallbackErr error) {\n   161→\targs := a.argsFor(command)\n   162→\tcmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, command, args...)\n   163→\tcmd.Dir = workDir\n   164→\tcmd.Stdin = strings.NewReader(prompt)\n   165→\n   166→\t// If we have a StatusWriter, stream stdout line-by-line; otherwise buffer.\n   167→\tif a.StatusWriter == nil {\n   168→\t\tvar stdoutBuf, stderrBuf bytes.Buffer\n   169→\t\tcmd.Stdout = &stdoutBuf\n   170→\t\tcmd.Stderr = &stderrBuf\n   171→\n   172→\t\trunErr := cmd.Run()\n   173→\t\tstdoutBytes := stdoutBuf.Bytes()\n   174→\t\treturn a.classifyResult(command, stdoutBytes, runErr)\n   175→\t}\n   176→\n   177→\t// Streaming path: pipe stdout through a scanner so we can emit lines live.\n   178→\tpipe, err := cmd.StdoutPipe()\n   179→\tif err != nil {\n   180→\t\treturn \"\", nil, fmt.Errorf(\"command %q stdout pipe: %w\", command, err)\n   181→\t}\n   182→\tcmd.Stderr = nil // discard stderr\n   183→\n   184→\tif err := cmd.Start(); err != nil {\n   185→\t\treturn \"\", nil, fmt.Errorf(\"command %q failed to start: %w\", command, err)\n   186→\t}\n   187→\n   188→\t// textBuf accumulates extracted text content for result extraction.\n   189→\t// rawBuf accumulates raw stdout for the output log file.\n   190→\tvar textBuf, rawBuf bytes.Buffer\n   191→\t// lineBuf accumulates text deltas into lines for streaming.\n   192→\tvar lineBuf strings.Builder\n   193→\n   194→\tscanner := bufio.NewScanner(pipe)\n   195→\tscanner.Buffer(make([]byte, 0, 256*1024), 1024*1024)\n   196→\tfor scanner.Scan() {\n   197→\t\traw := scanner.Bytes()\n   198→\t\trawBuf.Write(raw)\n   199→\t\trawBuf.WriteByte('\\n')\n   200→\n   201→\t\ttext := extractStreamText(raw)\n   202→\t\tif text == \"\" {\n   203→\t\t\tcontinue\n   204→\t\t}\n   205→\t\ttextBuf.WriteString(text)\n   206→\n   207→\t\t// Stream complete lines to StatusWriter as they form.\n   208→\t\tlineBuf.WriteString(text)\n   209→\t\tfor {\n   210→\t\t\ts := lineBuf.String()\n   211→\t\t\tidx := strings.IndexByte(s, '\\n')\n   212→\t\t\tif idx < 0 {\n   213→\t\t\t\tbreak\n   214→\t\t\t}\n   215→\t\t\ta.StatusWriter.Log(stepName, s[:idx])\n   216→\t\t\tlineBuf.Reset()\n   217→\t\t\tlineBuf.WriteString(s[idx+1:])\n   218→\t\t}\n   219→\t}\n   220→\t// Flush any remaining partial line.\n   221→\tif lineBuf.Len() > 0 {\n   222→\t\ta.StatusWriter.Log(stepName, lineBuf.String())\n   223→\t}\n   224→\tif scanErr := scanner.Err(); scanErr != nil {\n   225→\t\ta.StatusWriter.Log(stepName, fmt.Sprintf(\"[scan error: %v]\", scanErr))\n   226→\t}\n   227→\n   228→\twaitErr := cmd.Wait()\n   229→\t// Prefer extracted text (stream-json) for result classification; fall back\n   230→\t// to raw output for non-JSON commands (scripts, non-claude agents).\n   231→\tclassifyBuf := textBuf.Bytes()\n   232→\tif len(bytes.TrimSpace(classifyBuf)) == 0 {\n   233→\t\tclassifyBuf = rawBuf.Bytes()\n   234→\t}\n   235→\tresult, _, fallbackErr = a.classifyResult(command, classifyBuf, waitErr)\n   236→\treturn result, rawBuf.Bytes(), fallbackErr\n   237→}\n   238→\n   239→// classifyResult interprets the command's exit status and stdout to determine\n   240→// the step result.\n   241→func (a *Adapter) classifyResult(command string, stdoutBytes []byte, runErr error) (string, []byte, error) {\n   242→\tif runErr != nil {\n   243→\t\tif _, ok := runErr.(*exec.ExitError); !ok {\n   244→\t\t\t// Command failed to start (not found, permission denied, etc.)\n   245→\t\t\treturn \"\", nil, fmt.Errorf(\"command %q failed to start: %w\", command, runErr)\n   246→\t\t}\n   247→\t\t// Command ran but exited non-zero\n   248→\t\tmarkerResult, _, found := protocol.ExtractResult(stdoutBytes)\n   249→\t\tif found {\n   250→\t\t\treturn markerResult, stdoutBytes, nil\n   251→\t\t}\n   252→\t\treturn \"fail\", stdoutBytes, fmt.Errorf(\"command %q exited with error: %w\", command, runErr)\n   253→\t}\n   254→\n   255→\t// Command succeeded (exit 0)\n   256→\tif len(bytes.TrimSpace(stdoutBytes)) == 0 {\n   257→\t\treturn \"fail\", stdoutBytes, fmt.Errorf(\"command %q exited 0 but produced no output (auth/config issue?)\", command)\n   258→\t}\n   259→\tmarkerResult, _, found := protocol.ExtractResult(stdoutBytes)\n   260→\tresult := \"success\"\n   261→\tif found {\n   262→\t\tresult = markerResult\n   263→\t}\n   264→\treturn result, stdoutBytes, nil\n   265→}\n   266→\n   267→// extractStreamText parses a stream-json line and returns text content.\n   268→// It handles both content_block_delta (text_delta) events for streaming and\n   269→// result events for final output (which contains the CLOCHE_RESULT marker).\n   270→func extractStreamText(line []byte) string {\n   271→\t// Fast path: only parse lines that could contain text we care about.\n   272→\tif bytes.Contains(line, []byte(`\"text_delta\"`)) {\n   273→\t\tvar event struct {\n   274→\t\t\tType  string `json:\"type\"`\n   275→\t\t\tDelta struct {\n   276→\t\t\t\tType string `json:\"type\"`\n   277→\t\t\t\tText string `json:\"text\"`\n   278→\t\t\t} `json:\"delta\"`\n   279→\t\t}\n   280→\t\tif json.Unmarshal(line, &event) == nil &&\n   281→\t\t\tevent.Type == \"content_block_delta\" && event.Delta.Type == \"text_delta\" {\n   282→\t\t\treturn event.Delta.Text\n   283→\t\t}\n   284→\t}\n   285→\n   286→\t// Also extract the final result text (contains CLOCHE_RESULT marker).\n   287→\tif bytes.Contains(line, []byte(`\"result\"`)) && bytes.Contains(line, []byte(`\"subtype\"`)) {\n   288→\t\tvar event struct {\n   289→\t\t\tType   string `json:\"type\"`\n   290→\t\t\tResult string `json:\"result\"`\n   291→\t\t}\n   292→\t\tif json.Unmarshal(line, &event) == nil && event.Type == \"result\" {\n   293→\t\t\treturn event.Result\n   294→\t\t}\n   295→\t}\n   296→\n   297→\treturn \"\"\n   298→}\n   299→\n   300→func assemblePrompt(step *domain.Step, workDir, runID string) (string, error) {\n   301→\tvar parts []string\n   302→\n   303→\t// 1. Read system template from step config\n   304→\tif tmpl, ok := step.Config[\"prompt\"]; ok {\n   305→\t\tcontent, err := resolveContent(tmpl, workDir)\n   306→\t\tif err != nil {\n   307→\t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"reading prompt template: %w\", err)\n   308→\t\t}\n   309→\t\tparts = append(parts, content)\n   310→\t}\n   311→\n   312→\t// 2. Read user prompt from .cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt\n   313→\tuserPrompt := readUserPrompt(workDir, runID)\n   314→\tif userPrompt != \"\" {\n   315→\t\tparts = append(parts, \"## User Request\\n\"+userPrompt)\n   316→\t}\n   317→\n   318→\t// 3. Read feedback from .cloche/output/*.log (opt-in via step config)\n   319→\tif step.Config[\"feedback\"] == \"true\" {\n   320→\t\tfeedback := readFeedback(workDir)\n   321→\t\tif feedback != \"\" {\n   322→\t\t\tparts = append(parts, \"## Validation Output\\n\"+feedback)\n   323→\t\t}\n   324→\t}\n   325→\n   326→\t// 4. Result selection instructions\n   327→\tif len(step.Results) > 0 {\n   328→\t\tvar resultLines []string\n   329→\t\tresultLines = append(resultLines, \"## Result Selection\")\n   330→\t\tresultLines = append(resultLines, \"When you are finished, output exactly one of the following on its own line:\")\n   331→\t\tfor _, r := range step.Results {\n   332→\t\t\tresultLines = append(resultLines, protocol.ResultPrefix+r)\n   333→\t\t}\n   334→\t\tparts = append(parts, strings.Join(resultLines, \"\\n\"))\n   335→\t}\n   336→\n   337→\treturn strings.Join(parts, \"\\n\\n\"), nil\n   338→}\n   339→\n   340→// resolveContent handles file(\"path\") syntax or returns the string directly.\n   341→func resolveContent(value string, workDir string) (string, error) {\n   342→\t// Check for file(\"path\") syntax from DSL parser\n   343→\tif strings.HasPrefix(value, `file(\"`) && strings.HasSuffix(value, `\")`) {\n   344→\t\tpath := value[6 : len(value)-2]\n   345→\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(workDir, path))\n   346→\t\tif err != nil {\n   347→\t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"reading file %q: %w\", path, err)\n   348→\t\t}\n   349→\t\treturn string(data), nil\n   350→\t}\n   351→\treturn value, nil\n   352→}\n   353→\n   354→func readFeedback(workDir string) string {\n   355→\toutputDir := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"output\")\n   356→\tentries, err := os.ReadDir(outputDir)\n   357→\tif err != nil {\n   358→\t\treturn \"\"\n   359→\t}\n   360→\n   361→\tvar parts []string\n   362→\tfor _, entry := range entries {\n   363→\t\tif entry.IsDir() || !strings.HasSuffix(entry.Name(), \".log\") {\n   364→\t\t\tcontinue\n   365→\t\t}\n   366→\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(outputDir, entry.Name()))\n   367→\t\tif err != nil {\n   368→\t\t\tcontinue\n   369→\t\t}\n   370→\t\tcontent := strings.TrimSpace(string(data))\n   371→\t\tif content != \"\" {\n   372→\t\t\tstepName := strings.TrimSuffix(entry.Name(), \".log\")\n   373→\t\t\tparts = append(parts, fmt.Sprintf(\"### %s\\n```\\n%s\\n```\", stepName, content))\n   374→\t\t}\n   375→\t}\n   376→\n   377→\treturn strings.Join(parts, \"\\n\\n\")\n   378→}\n   379→\n   380→func readAttemptCount(workDir, stepName string) int {\n   381→\tpath := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"attempt_count\", stepName)\n   382→\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(path)\n   383→\tif err != nil {\n   384→\t\treturn 0\n   385→\t}\n   386→\tn, _ := strconv.Atoi(strings.TrimSpace(string(data)))\n   387→\treturn n\n   388→}\n   389→\n   390→// readUserPrompt reads the user prompt from .cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt.\n   391→func readUserPrompt(workDir, runID string) string {\n   392→\tif runID == \"\" {\n   393→\t\treturn \"\"\n   394→\t}\n   395→\tpath := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"prompt.txt\")\n   396→\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(path); err == nil {\n   397→\t\treturn string(data)\n   398→\t}\n   399→\treturn \"\"\n   400→}\n   401→\n   402→func incrementAttemptCount(workDir, stepName string) {\n   403→\tdir := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"attempt_count\")\n   404→\t_ = os.MkdirAll(dir, 0755)\n   405→\tcount := readAttemptCount(workDir, stepName) + 1\n   406→\t_ = os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(dir, stepName), []byte(strconv.Itoa(count)), 0644)\n   407→}\n   408→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e1389d09-7003-4c8d-9ad3-708dba903a1e","uuid":"32d00bd2-77a5-4bca-bc37-17b130dc9856","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go","content":"package prompt\n\nimport (\n\t\"bufio\"\n\t\"bytes\"\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"log\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"os/exec\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\t\"strconv\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/protocol\"\n)\n\n// DefaultAgentArgs maps known agent commands to their default arguments.\n// Commands not in this map receive no default arguments (prompt on stdin only).\nvar DefaultAgentArgs = map[string][]string{\n\t\"claude\": {\"-p\", \"--output-format\", \"stream-json\", \"--verbose\", \"--dangerously-skip-permissions\"},\n\t\"gemini\": {\"-p\"},\n\t\"codex\":  {\"--full-auto\"},\n}\n\ntype Adapter struct {\n\tCommands     []string // ordered fallback chain of agent commands\n\tExplicitArgs []string // if non-nil, overrides default args for all commands\n\tRunID        string\n\tStatusWriter *protocol.StatusWriter // optional: streams live output lines\n}\n\nfunc New() *Adapter {\n\treturn &Adapter{\n\t\tCommands: []string{\"claude\"},\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (a *Adapter) Name() string {\n\treturn \"prompt\"\n}\n\n// logMessage writes a message to the StatusWriter if available, otherwise to the standard logger.\nfunc (a *Adapter) logMessage(stepName, msg string) {\n\tif a.StatusWriter != nil {\n\t\ta.StatusWriter.Log(stepName, msg)\n\t} else {\n\t\tlog.Println(msg)\n\t}\n}\n\n// argsFor returns the arguments for the given command. If ExplicitArgs is set,\n// it is used for all commands. Otherwise, known agents get their default args.\nfunc (a *Adapter) argsFor(command string) []string {\n\tif a.ExplicitArgs != nil {\n\t\treturn a.ExplicitArgs\n\t}\n\tif args, ok := DefaultAgentArgs[command]; ok {\n\t\treturn args\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// ParseCommands splits a comma-separated agent_command string into individual\n// command names, trimming whitespace from each entry.\nfunc ParseCommands(s string) []string {\n\tparts := strings.Split(s, \",\")\n\tvar cmds []string\n\tfor _, p := range parts {\n\t\tp = strings.TrimSpace(p)\n\t\tif p != \"\" {\n\t\t\tcmds = append(cmds, p)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn cmds\n}\n\nfunc (a *Adapter) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (string, error) {\n\t// Check attempt count for retry limiting\n\tif maxStr, ok := step.Config[\"max_attempts\"]; ok {\n\t\tmax, err := strconv.Atoi(maxStr)\n\t\tif err == nil {\n\t\t\tcount := readAttemptCount(workDir, step.Name)\n\t\t\tif count >= max {\n\t\t\t\treturn \"give-up\", nil\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tincrementAttemptCount(workDir, step.Name)\n\n\t// Build the full prompt\n\tfullPrompt, err := assemblePrompt(step, workDir, a.RunID)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"assembling prompt: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\t// Try each command in the fallback chain\n\tvar lastResult string\n\tvar lastStdout []byte\n\tvar lastErr error\n\tran := false\n\n\tfor i, command := range a.Commands {\n\t\tresult, stdout, fallbackErr := a.tryCommand(ctx, command, fullPrompt, workDir, step.Name)\n\t\tlastResult = result\n\t\tlastStdout = stdout\n\t\tlastErr = fallbackErr\n\n\t\tif fallbackErr == nil {\n\t\t\tif i > 0 {\n\t\t\t\tmsg := fmt.Sprintf(\"[fallback] step %q: using agent %q (primary agents failed)\", step.Name, command)\n\t\t\t\ta.logMessage(step.Name, msg)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t}\n\t\tif stdout != nil {\n\t\t\tran = true\n\t\t}\n\t\t// Log the fallback attempt\n\t\tif i < len(a.Commands)-1 {\n\t\t\tmsg := fmt.Sprintf(\"[fallback] step %q: agent %q failed (%v), trying %q\", step.Name, command, fallbackErr, a.Commands[i+1])\n\t\t\ta.logMessage(step.Name, msg)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tif lastErr != nil && !ran && lastStdout == nil {\n\t\t// All commands failed to produce any output (e.g., all not found)\n\t\treturn \"\", lastErr\n\t}\n\n\tresult := lastResult\n\tif lastErr != nil {\n\t\t// Last command in chain crashed without a result marker\n\t\tresult = \"fail\"\n\t}\n\n\t// Write output file\n\toutputDir := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"output\")\n\tif mkErr := os.MkdirAll(outputDir, 0755); mkErr == nil {\n\t\t_ = os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(outputDir, step.Name+\".log\"), lastStdout, 0644)\n\t}\n\tprotocol.AppendHistory(workDir, step.Name, result, true, nil)\n\treturn result, nil\n}\n\n// tryCommand executes a single agent command and returns:\n//   - result: the step result name (e.g. \"success\", \"fail\")\n//   - stdout: captured stdout bytes\n//   - fallbackErr: nil if the result is definitive, non-nil if fallback-eligible\n//\n// Fallback-eligible conditions:\n//   - Command not found or failed to start (stdout will be nil)\n//   - Command exited non-zero without a CLOCHE_RESULT marker\n//\n// Definitive (non-fallback) conditions:\n//   - Command exited 0\n//   - Command exited non-zero but produced a CLOCHE_RESULT marker\nfunc (a *Adapter) tryCommand(ctx context.Context, command string, prompt string, workDir string, stepName string) (result string, stdout []byte, fallbackErr error) {\n\targs := a.argsFor(command)\n\tcmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, command, args...)\n\tcmd.Dir = workDir\n\tcmd.Stdin = strings.NewReader(prompt)\n\n\t// If we have a StatusWriter, stream stdout line-by-line; otherwise buffer.\n\tif a.StatusWriter == nil {\n\t\tvar stdoutBuf, stderrBuf bytes.Buffer\n\t\tcmd.Stdout = &stdoutBuf\n\t\tcmd.Stderr = &stderrBuf\n\n\t\trunErr := cmd.Run()\n\t\tstdoutBytes := stdoutBuf.Bytes()\n\t\treturn a.classifyResult(command, stdoutBytes, runErr)\n\t}\n\n\t// Streaming path: pipe stdout through a scanner so we can emit lines live.\n\tpipe, err := cmd.StdoutPipe()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", nil, fmt.Errorf(\"command %q stdout pipe: %w\", command, err)\n\t}\n\tcmd.Stderr = nil // discard stderr\n\n\tif err := cmd.Start(); err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", nil, fmt.Errorf(\"command %q failed to start: %w\", command, err)\n\t}\n\n\t// textBuf accumulates extracted text content for result extraction.\n\t// rawBuf accumulates raw stdout for the output log file.\n\tvar textBuf, rawBuf bytes.Buffer\n\t// lineBuf accumulates text deltas into lines for streaming.\n\tvar lineBuf strings.Builder\n\n\tscanner := bufio.NewScanner(pipe)\n\tscanner.Buffer(make([]byte, 0, 256*1024), 1024*1024)\n\tfor scanner.Scan() {\n\t\traw := scanner.Bytes()\n\t\trawBuf.Write(raw)\n\t\trawBuf.WriteByte('\\n')\n\n\t\ttext := extractStreamText(raw)\n\t\tif text == \"\" {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\ttextBuf.WriteString(text)\n\n\t\t// Stream complete lines to StatusWriter as they form.\n\t\tlineBuf.WriteString(text)\n\t\tfor {\n\t\t\ts := lineBuf.String()\n\t\t\tidx := strings.IndexByte(s, '\\n')\n\t\t\tif idx < 0 {\n\t\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\ta.StatusWriter.Log(stepName, s[:idx])\n\t\t\tlineBuf.Reset()\n\t\t\tlineBuf.WriteString(s[idx+1:])\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\t// Flush any remaining partial line.\n\tif lineBuf.Len() > 0 {\n\t\ta.StatusWriter.Log(stepName, lineBuf.String())\n\t}\n\tif scanErr := scanner.Err(); scanErr != nil {\n\t\ta.StatusWriter.Log(stepName, fmt.Sprintf(\"[scan error: %v]\", scanErr))\n\t}\n\n\twaitErr := cmd.Wait()\n\t// Prefer extracted text (stream-json) for result classification; fall back\n\t// to raw output for non-JSON commands (scripts, non-claude agents).\n\tclassifyBuf := textBuf.Bytes()\n\tif len(bytes.TrimSpace(classifyBuf)) == 0 {\n\t\tclassifyBuf = rawBuf.Bytes()\n\t}\n\tresult, _, fallbackErr = a.classifyResult(command, classifyBuf, waitErr)\n\treturn result, rawBuf.Bytes(), fallbackErr\n}\n\n// classifyResult interprets the command's exit status and stdout to determine\n// the step result.\nfunc (a *Adapter) classifyResult(command string, stdoutBytes []byte, runErr error) (string, []byte, error) {\n\tif runErr != nil {\n\t\tif _, ok := runErr.(*exec.ExitError); !ok {\n\t\t\t// Command failed to start (not found, permission denied, etc.)\n\t\t\treturn \"\", nil, fmt.Errorf(\"command %q failed to start: %w\", command, runErr)\n\t\t}\n\t\t// Command ran but exited non-zero\n\t\tmarkerResult, _, found := protocol.ExtractResult(stdoutBytes)\n\t\tif found {\n\t\t\treturn markerResult, stdoutBytes, nil\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn \"fail\", stdoutBytes, fmt.Errorf(\"command %q exited with error: %w\", command, runErr)\n\t}\n\n\t// Command succeeded (exit 0)\n\tif len(bytes.TrimSpace(stdoutBytes)) == 0 {\n\t\treturn \"fail\", stdoutBytes, fmt.Errorf(\"command %q exited 0 but produced no output (auth/config issue?)\", command)\n\t}\n\tmarkerResult, _, found := protocol.ExtractResult(stdoutBytes)\n\tresult := \"success\"\n\tif found {\n\t\tresult = markerResult\n\t}\n\treturn result, stdoutBytes, nil\n}\n\n// extractStreamText parses a stream-json line and returns text content.\n// It handles both content_block_delta (text_delta) events for streaming and\n// result events for final output (which contains the CLOCHE_RESULT marker).\nfunc extractStreamText(line []byte) string {\n\t// Fast path: only parse lines that could contain text we care about.\n\tif bytes.Contains(line, []byte(`\"text_delta\"`)) {\n\t\tvar event struct {\n\t\t\tType  string `json:\"type\"`\n\t\t\tDelta struct {\n\t\t\t\tType string `json:\"type\"`\n\t\t\t\tText string `json:\"text\"`\n\t\t\t} `json:\"delta\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tif json.Unmarshal(line, &event) == nil &&\n\t\t\tevent.Type == \"content_block_delta\" && event.Delta.Type == \"text_delta\" {\n\t\t\treturn event.Delta.Text\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Also extract the final result text (contains CLOCHE_RESULT marker).\n\tif bytes.Contains(line, []byte(`\"result\"`)) && bytes.Contains(line, []byte(`\"subtype\"`)) {\n\t\tvar event struct {\n\t\t\tType   string `json:\"type\"`\n\t\t\tResult string `json:\"result\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tif json.Unmarshal(line, &event) == nil && event.Type == \"result\" {\n\t\t\treturn event.Result\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn \"\"\n}\n\nfunc assemblePrompt(step *domain.Step, workDir, runID string) (string, error) {\n\tvar parts []string\n\n\t// 1. Read system template from step config\n\tif tmpl, ok := step.Config[\"prompt\"]; ok {\n\t\tcontent, err := resolveContent(tmpl, workDir)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"reading prompt template: %w\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tparts = append(parts, content)\n\t}\n\n\t// 2. Read user prompt from .cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt\n\tuserPrompt := readUserPrompt(workDir, runID)\n\tif userPrompt != \"\" {\n\t\tparts = append(parts, \"## User Request\\n\"+userPrompt)\n\t}\n\n\t// 3. Read feedback from .cloche/output/*.log (opt-in via step config)\n\tif step.Config[\"feedback\"] == \"true\" {\n\t\tfeedback := readFeedback(workDir)\n\t\tif feedback != \"\" {\n\t\t\tparts = append(parts, \"## Validation Output\\n\"+feedback)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// 4. Result selection instructions\n\tif len(step.Results) > 0 {\n\t\tvar resultLines []string\n\t\tresultLines = append(resultLines, \"## Result Selection\")\n\t\tresultLines = append(resultLines, \"When you are finished, output exactly one of the following on its own line:\")\n\t\tfor _, r := range step.Results {\n\t\t\tresultLines = append(resultLines, protocol.ResultPrefix+r)\n\t\t}\n\t\tparts = append(parts, strings.Join(resultLines, \"\\n\"))\n\t}\n\n\treturn strings.Join(parts, \"\\n\\n\"), nil\n}\n\n// resolveContent handles file(\"path\") syntax or returns the string directly.\nfunc resolveContent(value string, workDir string) (string, error) {\n\t// Check for file(\"path\") syntax from DSL parser\n\tif strings.HasPrefix(value, `file(\"`) && strings.HasSuffix(value, `\")`) {\n\t\tpath := value[6 : len(value)-2]\n\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(workDir, path))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"reading file %q: %w\", path, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn string(data), nil\n\t}\n\treturn value, nil\n}\n\nfunc readFeedback(workDir string) string {\n\toutputDir := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"output\")\n\tentries, err := os.ReadDir(outputDir)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n\n\tvar parts []string\n\tfor _, entry := range entries {\n\t\tif entry.IsDir() || !strings.HasSuffix(entry.Name(), \".log\") {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(outputDir, entry.Name()))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tcontent := strings.TrimSpace(string(data))\n\t\tif content != \"\" {\n\t\t\tstepName := strings.TrimSuffix(entry.Name(), \".log\")\n\t\t\tparts = append(parts, fmt.Sprintf(\"### %s\\n```\\n%s\\n```\", stepName, content))\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn strings.Join(parts, \"\\n\\n\")\n}\n\nfunc readAttemptCount(workDir, stepName string) int {\n\tpath := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"attempt_count\", stepName)\n\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(path)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn 0\n\t}\n\tn, _ := strconv.Atoi(strings.TrimSpace(string(data)))\n\treturn n\n}\n\n// readUserPrompt reads the user prompt from .cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt.\nfunc readUserPrompt(workDir, runID string) string {\n\tif runID == \"\" {\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n\tpath := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"prompt.txt\")\n\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(path); err == nil {\n\t\treturn string(data)\n\t}\n\treturn \"\"\n}\n\nfunc incrementAttemptCount(workDir, stepName string) {\n\tdir := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"attempt_count\")\n\t_ = os.MkdirAll(dir, 0755)\n\tcount := readAttemptCount(workDir, stepName) + 1\n\t_ = os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(dir, stepName), []byte(strconv.Itoa(count)), 0644)\n}\n","numLines":408,"startLine":1,"totalLines":408}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Ris2iWK1dfHXwJaATBrDPE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me check for discrepancies between the source code and docs/USAGE.md:\n\n1. **`cloche init` flags**:\n   - Source code (init.go:148): `--base-image` with default `cloche-base:latest`\n   - Usage line (main.go:84): `init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <image>]`\n   - Docs (USAGE.md:116-117): `cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--image <base>]` with flag `--image <base>` and default `ubuntu:24.04`\n   - The docs have the flag name wrong—it should be `--base-image` not `--image`, and the default is `cloche-base:latest` not `ubuntu:24.04`.\n\n2. **`cloche init` description**: The docs claim it creates config.toml and prompt templates, which matches the code, but I need to verify the other files mentioned like `host.cloche`, `scripts/prepare-prompt.sh`, and the `version` file to see if those are actually created.\n\n3. **Agent default args**: There's a mismatch between what the code specifies and what the docs say. The code has Claude using `stream-json` output format with `--verbose`, but the docs claim it uses `text` format and don't mention `--verbose` at all.\n\n4. **Gemini and Codex defaults**: The code shows Gemini gets `-p` while Codex gets `--full-auto`, but the docs don't clearly specify these defaults.\n\n5. **Project setup section**: I'm checking what the docs say about the default Dockerfile configuration.\n\n6. **`agent_args` override**: The docs mention this can be overridden at step or workflow level, and I can confirm the code handles this in runner.go.\n\n7. **`CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` env var**: The docs reference this and the code does check for it, so that's consistent.\n\n8. **Fallback rules**: Now I'm verifying what the docs say about command fallback behavior against the actual code implementation. I'm noticing there's a discrepancy between the documentation and the actual behavior — the docs say \"Exit 0 — use result (no fallback)\" but the code actually triggers a fallback when exit 0 produces empty output, which seems like a reasonable edge case the docs just didn't mention. The real issues I need to focus on are the parameter mismatches: `--image` should be `--base-image` with a different default, and the Claude default arguments are missing `--verbose` and using the wrong output format.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8598,"cache_read_input_tokens":33697,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8598},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e1389d09-7003-4c8d-9ad3-708dba903a1e","uuid":"244f2655-ebc8-4381-a7e4-4efea63d37bf"}
